  "text": "A further study has shown that the densely nondifferentiable Cauchy horizons are quite common [CITATION_1] . Let R 2,1 be the 3 -dimensional Minkowski space-time. Let Σ be the surface t = 0, and let K be a compact, convex subset of Σ. Let ∂K denote the boundary of K.",
